<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/132402-in-the-novel-daru-is-just-a-product-that">In the novel , Daru is just a product that our system produces , a product flawed with superficial coatings like jealousy, guilt and poverty , but deep inside he is as innocent as child. The best part is how the world is from Ozi&#39;s perspective, everyone sees the world through his clean mirror. 
my fav line in the novel 
&quot;I never lie&quot;, I lied 

Worth reading .</a>
