<div id="review_2093500997" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2093500997" />
    <a title="Shishir Chaudhary" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4540373-shishir-chaudhary"><img alt="Shishir Chaudhary" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1489846870p2/4540373.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2093500997?book_show_action=true">Aug 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shishir Chaudhary" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shishir Chaudhary" href="/user/show/4540373-shishir-chaudhary">Shishir Chaudhary</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/10927990-moth-smoke">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4540373-shishir-chaudhary?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2093500997" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1434059935307313438">This is exactly the kind of book I have been wanting to read for a long time - character driven, lucid narrative, gripping story. This is the exact opposite of coming-of-age genre but is equally, if not more, enchanting. Mohsin, at the pinnacle of his creativity, tells the story of the decline of Darashikoh (or, Daru) while he scoots through a lethal affair with his best friend&apos;s wife amidst weed, hash and heroine. Joining him, is obviously the equally flawed but a powerful and sexy Mumtaz (the </span>
  <span id="freeText1434059935307313438" style="display:none">This is exactly the kind of book I have been wanting to read for a long time - character driven, lucid narrative, gripping story. This is the exact opposite of coming-of-age genre but is equally, if not more, enchanting. Mohsin, at the pinnacle of his creativity, tells the story of the decline of Darashikoh (or, Daru) while he scoots through a lethal affair with his best friend's wife amidst weed, hash and heroine. Joining him, is obviously the equally flawed but a powerful and sexy Mumtaz (the wife of the best friend), Aurangzeb or Ozi (the best friend) and Murad (the learned, intellectual drug supplier).<br /><br />Mohsin Hamid sets the story in the backdrop of nuclear tests by India and Pakistan, the rivalry and associated conflicts and celebrations reflecting in the lives of characters, confused about their respective places in the Pakistani society of the time.<br /><br />It is one of the best books I have read. Strongly recommended!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1434059935307313438" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


